SIMPLE: darkly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Darkly
<hw>Dark"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>With imperfect light,
clearness, or knowledge; obscurely; dimly; blindly;
uncertainly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What fame to future times conveys but <qex>darkly</qex> down.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>so softly dark and <qex>darkly</qex> pure.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>With a dark, gloomy, cruel, or menacing
look.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Looking <qex>darkly</qex> at the clerguman.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Darkness</ent>⟦br⟧
